name: employee_system
description: Practice project to learn microservice architecture

name: microservice-auth
description: The primary purpose of this microservice is to handle user identity verification (authentication) and grant or deny access to various system resources based on the user's permissions (authorization).

name: Backend-Task-Management-System
description: Designed and developed a task management system using Java, Spring Boot, RESTful APIs, and Microservices.

name: freight-mileage-toll-calculation-system
description: A solution tailored for the logistics and transportation industry. Built on a robust microservices architecture with Go.

name: Integrated-Energy-Management-System
description: The project involves creating an integrated system by connecting the microservices, deploying them on a virtualized infrastructure, and ensuring security features are in place. Configure the network to enable proper communication among the dockerized components. Ensure service authentication and authorization using JWT among these components.

name: ChitChat
description: An assessment project to showcase a microservices-based chat system, utilizing Node.js, React, Apollo, RabbitMQ, and Firestore.

name: Constructions-Inspection-system-for-the-City-of-Kigali
description: I designed this system as I was conducting research in the City of Kigali with the aim to ease the process of capturing information from construction sites and sharing reports to stakeholders. The system's architecture is microservice with the front-end application built using React and the backend built using Spring Boot.

name: Bulkhead-Patterns-Presentation
description: The bulkhead pattern in microservices design involves isolating services into separate execution environments (e.g., threads, processes) to contain faults and prevent cascading failures, thereby enhancing system resilience and fault tolerance.

name: TrainX
description: The fitness tracker application's architecture is set up to take advantage of new technologies and Microservices Architecture to build a dependable and expandable system. The programme, which was created with C# and Asp.net, takes a user-centric strategy while smoothly integrating CRUD functions with Web Services.
